  "body": "\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.9.12-stable\r\nGit Commit: b6f1c8dcc058a936955eb8e5766e2962218924bc\r\nGit Commit Date: 20200316\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [65 64 63]\r\nGo Version: go1.13.8\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/local/go\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nJSON RPC server should handle `Connection: close` and release socket\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nGeth let socket open even after client close the connection causing the OS handling it through `CLOSE_WAIT` `TIME_WAIT` mechanism \r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nIssue thousands requests in order to exhaust file descriptors (not sure it is FD as i'm below system limit).\r\n\r\nAt some point rpc responds erratically \r\n\r\n```\r\n netstat -naltp | grep TIME|wc -l\r\n(Not all processes could be identified, non-owned process info\r\n will not be shown, you would have to be root to see it all.)\r\n0\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\nnetstat -naltp | grep TIME|wc -l\r\n(Not all processes could be identified, non-owned process info\r\n will not be shown, you would have to be root to see it all.)\r\n13673\r\n```\r\n",
