    "body": "@karalabe \r\n- I used a single host and `bluebird` `Promise.map` using web3js client with 10 request per map\r\n- I then noticed that web3js was sending `Connection: keep-alive` so i hacked the underlying library `xhr2-cookies/dist/xml-http-request.js` in order to force it to send `Connection: close`\r\n\r\nI had something like 100 000 balance to query (both ethereum and ERC20 one).\r\n\r\nI finally dropped `Promise.map` and iterated one by one up to completion, i still had more than 8000 TIME_WAIT connection by the time the script finished\r\n\r\nI'm sorry i can't come with a reproducer as I completely removed the `Promise.map` part from my script but roughly it was an async for loop  chunking a large array per 10 block requesting `web3.eth.getBalance` and `web3.eth.call(balanceOfPayload)`\r\n",
